race.comment: HURRICANE MIST (1) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at The Meadows over 525m behind South Thailand (31.10) in a Grade 5. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. MONTANA ICON (7) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at this track in a handy 28.78 beating Regal Barry. Leading chance again. LILLY LOUD MOUTH (2) had the drop on the lead from a soft draw and drew clear to score (26.50) at Geelong in Grade 5 over 460m. One of main contenders. FIRE WIRE (4) was in the money last start despite a big quote and is likely to feature again.
